      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HELLO NEMO (2) took the sit on the lead from a low draw but levelled up and led around the bend to score (22.91) at this track in a Grade 5 over 401m. Has a strong record out of this box with two wins and a minor placing from three starts. Well placed and will be tough to beat. MIDNIGHT ARROW (8) has a moderate overall strike-rate. Hit the board with a minor placing last time when third (23.06) at this track. Solid record at the distance winning three races. Leading chance. GULL WING (7) was well supported last time but could only manage second (23.01), beaten 1.75 lengths. Overdue and gets her chance. SPRING SIGNAL (4) was unplaced here last start but gets her chance to atone.",
